LA CROSSE, Wis. (WXOW) - The Green Bay Packers are coming to Onalaska in April.
The team announced their annual Packers Tailgate Tour stops for this year.
It begins in Milwaukee on April 8, stops in Madison on April 9, Onalaska on April 10, Wausau on April 11, and Green Bay on April 12.
The public event is at the Stoney Creek Hotel in Onalaska from 6-8 p.m. with doors opening at 5 p.m.
It's hosted by the Hunger Task Force.
There's 325 tickets available for the fundraising event. Each ticket is $75 per person.
They're available at the Hunger Task Force website.
On the tour this year are current and former players including current players Josh Jacobs, Tucker Kraft and Lukas Van Ness and alumni players Ahman Green, Jermichael Finley and John Michels on the tour bus along with Packers President/CEO Mark Murphy.
It's expected that during the tour, they'll stop at schools, hospitals, and businesses. Those details weren't released by the team.
